key-wdi2-NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG.def: Inflation as measured by the annual growth rate of the GDP implicit deflator shows the rate of price change in the economy as a whole. The GDP implicit deflator is the ratio of GDP in current local currency to GDP in constant local currency.
key-wdi2-NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG.name: GDP Growth (annual %)
key-wdi2-NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG.source: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.
